Why hibernate & why not jdbc ??

JDBC is a low-level API that requires developers to write SQL queries, manage database connections, transactions, and manually map database rows to Java objects. 
Hibernate is an ORM framework built on top of JDBC that automates these tasks. It converts Java objects into database records and vice versa, reducing boilerplate code, 
improving maintainability, and providing advanced features such as caching, lazy loading, and relationship mapping. Hibernate internally uses JDBC to communicate with the 
database, so it simplifies development rather than replacing JDBC.

